<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="1" id="19fb1228-db7a-53db-a724-0ba9fae0f70b" activityNameId="21ef521c-d14a-4910-9162-3171246f56c3" parentActivityId="818ee911-0a03-5952-a11d-d895c6b8829d" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">market for residue from Na-dichromate production</activityName>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">The activity starts with the input from the treatment processes.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">A market for a material for treatment (wastes or recyclables) ends with the provision of treatment, i.e. a mix of treatment providers, to activities that generate the reference product as a waste/by-product.</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This is a market activity, representing a treatment mix. In the case of products needing treatment, market mixes are supplied by the activities treating the product in the geography defined by the market, and they supply the activities needing to treat the product, as they have generated it as a by-product in the Undefined processes (present as a negative input in system models). Transport to the treating facility or losses are also accounted in this type of markets, when relevant. This is the market for 'residue from Na-dichromate production'' in Global geography. Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.</text>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="9a63625a-358b-4c1d-bf95-50ba038a759b">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">3821:Treatment and disposal of non-hazardous waste</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="7846b897-7c04-4f9f-b607-2b83fcd9a74c">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">RoW</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The disposal mix is country-specific for Global geography.</text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The dataset supplies a disposal mix (technology mix) of 'residue from Na-dichromate production'' to the respective waste producing activities.</text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="2010-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true"/>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
